<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: POMONA; MOTHER CHARGED 
IN DEATH OF BABY THROWN TO DOGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A teen-aged woman with two children was charged with murder Thursday in the 
death of her third child, a newborn boy who may have been dead when he was 
thrown into a yard occupied by two pit bulls. 
</P>
<P>
 Araceli Banda Garcia, 19, is scheduled to be arraigned Nov. 17. 
</P>
<P>
 Garcia, arrested Tuesday and held on $1-million bail, is charged with single 
counts of murder and child endangerment in the death of her baby, whose body 
was found last Friday afternoon in the 500 block of West Orange Grove Avenue in 
Pomona. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputy Dist. Atty. Garcy Hearnsberger said an autopsy indicated the nine-pound 
boy suffered a crushing injury to his head and a puncture in the chest, which 
the coroner's office believes caused the death.  
</P>
<P>
 Authorities believe Garcia gave birth to the baby Friday morning, killed him 
and threw the body over the back fence.  
</P>
<P>
 Investigators initially believed that one or both of the pit bulls had mauled 
the baby, whose body was missing an arm and testicles. But the large dog was 
penned up and the other was a puppy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
