METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: ENCINO; WOMAN GETS 45 
DAYS IN JAIL IN HIT-AND-RUN ACCIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An Encino woman will spend 45 days in jail and 45 days on a Caltrans work crew 
for hitting a 9-year-old girl with her car and fleeing the scene, the city 
attorney's office said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Mona Dowidar, 47, was also placed on three years of summary probation by Van 
Nuys Municipal Judge Michael Knight. 
</P>
<P>
 Dowidar was sentenced after a jury found her guilty of hit and run with injury 
after a four-day trial, Deputy City Atty. Elijah Richardson said. 
</P>
<P>
 The incident occurred the evening of July 29 as Dowidar was northbound on 
Yarmouth Avenue near Margate Street in Encino.  
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses said the victim stepped into the street in front of Dowidar's car, 
which struck the child, slightly injuring her. They said Dowidar continued on 
without stopping. 
</P>
<P>
 A Whittier man jumped into his car and followed Dowidar into a parking lot in 
the 17900 block of Ventura Boulevard, Richardson said. Dowidar was later 
arrested. 
</P>
<P>
 The child was treated at a hospital for cuts to her leg and released. 
</P>
