<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; GANG 
MEMBER SOUGHT IN KILLING OF CHEERLEADER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Los Angeles police were searching for a gang member suspected of killing a 
Dorsey High School cheerleader who may have inadvertently gotten mixed up in a 
robbery attempt.  
</P>
<P>
 Detectives said fingerprints and other evidence found at the crime scene on 
Oct. 28 helped them identify Carlton Maurice Gladden, 24, as a suspect in the 
killing. 
</P>
<P>
 Anitra Jolie Watson, 17, was shot several times execution style inside a 
duplex near Haas Avenue and Century Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
 Detectives said Watson was killed in an area police have called a drug hot 
spot. She was there when a robbery attempt took place. 
</P>
<P>
 "It may have been a drug rip-off or it may have been a straight robbery; we do 
not know," said Lt. Sergio Robleto.  
</P>
<P>
 "She was there at the location at a time when there was possibly a robbery 
going to take place, a robbery of the occupants of the location," Robleto said. 
</P>
<P>
 "Somehow or other it appears somebody may have mistaken her for one of the 
assailants and then subsequently executed her." 
</P>
