<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 When you think of Irvine, think apartments. 
</P>
<P>
 A recent study by a market research firm rated Irvine as South County's 
premier apartment destination, with an occupancy rate of 98.6%. 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Hills ranked second with a 98.3% occupancy rate, followed by Newport 
Beach at 98%, according to Research Network. 
</P>
<P>
 But Irvine takes second place when it comes to average monthly rental rates. 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Beach has the highest average rent in South County -- $987 -- with 
Irvine trailing close behind with an average rent of $962 a month. Today 
</P>
<P>
 Placentia's sixth annual Veteran's Day Observance Program takes place at 10 
a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The guest speaker for the event is Col. M.J. McCarthy. He will give a speech 
entitled "To Lay Down One's Life for You, Brother." 
</P>
<P>
 The service is designed to honor Placentia veterans and others who have fallen 
while defending their country. 
</P>
<P>
 The event will be at the Placentia Civic Center, 411 E. Chapman Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (714) 993-8117. 
