<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: QUAKE AID CENTERS TO CLOSE FOR HOLIDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG RIPPEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Due to Veterans Day, federal and state officials will close their earthquake 
assistance centers today and Saturday in Fillmore and Simi Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 Telephone services for earthquake assistance also will be unavailable today 
and Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 The offices, jointly operated by the state Office of Emergency Services and 
the Federal Emergency Management Agency, will reopen to the public on Monday. 
So will telephone services. 
</P>
<P>
 In the wake of the Jan. 17 earthquake, individuals, families and businesses 
have been able to register for assistance at the centers during business hours 
Monday through Friday and 9 a.m. to 1 p.m. Saturday. They may register by 
calling 1-800-462-9029. 
</P>
<P>
 For those seeking assistance, including Small Business Administration loans, 
the registration deadline is Nov. 17 -- the 10-month anniversary of the 
Northridge earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
 The Simi Valley office is at 59 Tierra Rejada Road and the Fillmore office is 
at 552 Sespe Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 General information is available at 1-800-525-0321. GREG RIPPEE 
</P>
</TEXT>
