<HEADLINE>
<P>
ST. JOHN KNITS FINDS NEW PLACE TO CALL HOME; HEADQUARTERS: THE WOMEN'S CLOTHING 
MANUFACTURER DECIDES TO STAY IN IRVINE AND WILL CONSOLIDATE HALF OF ITS 
OPERATIONS INTO A 161,000-SQUARE-FOOT BUILDING ON MICHELSON DRIVE. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DEBORA VRANA, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After searching for more than a year for a new headquarters building, St. John 
Knits Inc. said Thursday it has found one across town. 
</P>
<P>
 The Irvine-based manufacturer of women's clothing said it will consolidate 
about half of its existing Orange County operations into a large one-story 
building at the corner of Michelson Drive and Jamboree Road. 
</P>
<P>
 "We decided to stay in Irvine. We've been here for more than 15 years, and our 
employees all love the area. We're just moving down the road," said Bob Gray, 
chairman and chief executive officer. 
</P>
<P>
 In its search for a new home, the company had considered constructing a 
building on several Southern California sites, including one in Costa Mesa. 
Instead, St. John said, it has signed an agreement with Varian Associates, an 
Irvine investor group that owns real estate across Orange County, for a 
161,000-square-foot building at 2722 Michelson Drive. The property is valued at 
about $8 million. 
</P>
<P>
 St. John Knits and the investor group will own and manage the property as 
partners. Varian Associates will also contribute about $500,000 in cash for the 
project, St. John Knits said, and the clothing company will contribute $3.5 
million for building improvements. 
</P>
<P>
 Now occupied by computer hardware maker AmeriQuest Technologies Inc., the 
building will be remodeled to house St. John's corporate headquarters, design 
center and manufacturing operations. After extensive modifications, St. John 
Knits expects to move in by mid-1995. 
</P>
<P>
 AmeriQuest officials could not be reached Thursday to comment on their 
company's plans or confirm when its lease expires. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's a high-visibility corner, and we're a high-visibility firm. We want the 
people here to see where we make our product," Gray said. "Hopefully this will 
hold us for the next 10 years." 
</P>
<P>
 St. John Knits said it has also signed a letter of intent to lease an 
adjoining property that includes 120,000 square feet of industrial and storage 
space. St. John will convert facilities at its current 71,000-square-foot 
headquarters at 17422 Darian into manufacturing space. 
</P>
<P>
 St. John Knits has had healthy returns this year. For the quarter ended July 
31, the company reported a profit of $3.5 million, or 43 cents a share, up 40% 
from earnings of $2.5 million, or 31 cents a share, for the same period a year 
earlier. Revenue for the quarter increased 19% to $29.7 million from $25 
million. For the first nine months of its fiscal year, the company's profit was 
up 38% to $9.9 million. 
</P>
<P>
 The company's stock was up 12 1/2 cents to close at $30.87 a share in New York 
Stock Exchange trading Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
