<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIRST INTERSTATE TO SCALE BACK IN VENTURA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVID W. MYERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 First Interstate Bank, trying to digest its August purchase of Bank of A. Levy 
in Ventura County, said Thursday that it will close six branch offices in the 
county, eliminate up to 100 jobs and sell Levy's headquarters building in the 
city of Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 The two banks combined now have 25 offices and employ about 350 people in 
Ventura County.First Interstate said those workers may reapply for the 250 jobs 
in the 19 branches that First Interstate will own in the area after the 
consolidation is completed next April. 
</P>
<P>
 First Interstate said current employees at both banks will also be given a 
chance to apply for jobs elsewhere in First Interstate's 13-state system, 
although an undetermined number will have to be laid off. 
</P>
<P>
 First Interstate also said it will sell A. Levy's 10-acre headquarters complex 
in Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 A. Levy, founded 112 years ago, played a major role in transforming the 
once-rural region into a budding metropolis. First Interstate has more than 400 
offices and $25 billion in assets in California alone. DAVID W. MYERS 
</P>
</TEXT>
