<HEADLINE>
<P>
OC HIGH: STUDENT NEWS AND VIEWS; INLINE; EMOTIONAL SEASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The holidays can be tough emotionally for teens as well as others. Beating the 
holiday blues is the subject of a daylong presentation Saturday at Barnes & 
Noble Bookstore in Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
 In a 2 p.m. session directed specifically at teen-agers, Dr. Lawrence Budner 
of Orange will offer advice on overcoming excessive self-absorption, which, in 
Scrooge-like fashion, can destroy the potential for meaningful holiday 
experiences. 
</P>
<P>
 Other topics will be presented hourly, beginning with "Exercise & Nutrition" 
at 9 a.m. and ending with "The Value of Humor" at 4 p.m. At MainPlace, 2800 M. 
Main St., Santa Ana. (714) 667-0313. Getting Ahead 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Alamitos High School's dropout prevention program has gotten a boost 
with a $33,050 state grant designed to integrate technology and assist limited 
English-proficient pupils. 
</P>
<P>
 The Garden Grove school will use the funds to expand an existing dropout 
prevention program by creating a multimedia center in the library. Computerized 
learning stations will be established to help at-risk students of limited 
English ability and their families improve their language skills. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA111194-0186 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 097550 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
November 11, 1994, Friday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Life & Style; Part E; Page 3; Column 1; View Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
