<HEADLINE>
<P>
RSVP / ORANGE COUNTY; SILVER: ELEMENT OF ROMANCE; ALL THAT GLITTERS IS GALA 
APPAREL AT A LE MERIDIEN BALL SALUTING CHAPMAN GENERAL HOSPITAL. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROSE APODACA JONES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tradition calls for silver on a 25th anniversary and so out came silver bow 
ties, brooches and mesh bags Saturday for the Silvery Moon gala at Le 
Meridien's ballroom in Newport Beach saluting Chapman General Hospital.  
</P>
<P>
 The 400 guests attending the event -- many doctors, technicians and nurses 
from CGH -- were encouraged to don something silver at the black-tie 
event.Most, however, shunned the stunning silver fashions in season and opted 
instead for minimal touches, such as cuff links or earrings against customary 
black attire. 
</P>
<P>
 A few dared to sparkle with sterling knit or lace dresses and pantsuits. 
Others proved more stylistically daring in metallic sequins or beads. 
</P>
<P>
 After dinner, revelers danced to Bill Medley of the Righteous Brothers, who 
certainly wooed the guests with his soulful voice and good humor. The mood 
couldn't have been more romantic with the glittery moons, silver stars and 
white lights decorating the room. 
</P>
<P>
 And as typical of professionals who have dedicated their lives to helping 
others, proceeds from the event will benefit the nonprofit Chapman/Orange 
Community Health Foundation, which provides health education programs to the 
community. The event netted $25,000. ROSE APODACA JONES 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA111194-0188 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 097552 </DOCID>
