<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: PACOIMA; PARK TO BE DEDICATED TO LATE RITCHIE VALENS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF SCHNAUFER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fans of the late rock 'n' roll legend Ritchie Valens are invited to Pacoima on 
Saturday to celebrate the dedication of the Ritchie Valens Recreation Center. 
</P>
<P>
 The event, to be held from 11:30 a.m. to 4 p.m., renames Paxton Park after 
Ritchie, a Pacoima native.The park is located at 10736 Laurel Canyon Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
 Expected to appear at the ribbon-cutting ceremony are family members of 
Ritchie's, along with Los Angeles City Councilman Richard Alarcon, who proposed 
the name change in June. The Department of Parks and Recreation Board of 
Commissioners and the City Council later approved the change. 
</P>
<P>
 Entertainment will include the Ernie Valens band, Shaken and several other 
musical groups. 
</P>
<P>
 The name change is part of a community effort to inspire pride and 
self-esteem. Born Richard Valenzuela in Pacoima, Ritchie climbed out of this 
working-class neighborhood to become a rock icon in the late 1950s. His career 
and life were cut short, however, when he was killed at the age of 17 in a 1959 
plane crash along with Buddy Holly and J.P. (The Big Bopper) Richardson. JEFF 
SCHNAUFER 
</P>
</TEXT>
