VALLEYWIDE FOCUS: BENEFIT TO AID SHELTER FOR BATTERED WOMEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ERIC SLATER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In West Hollywood Sunday, they will rock 'n' roll for the safety of battered 
women. 
</P>
<P>
 Dubbed the Domestic Violence Consciousness Fair, 11 bands -- including Fem 2 
Fem, Load and the Paul Korda Band -- will turn up the volume and turn proceeds 
over to Haven Hills Family Violence Center, the San Fernando Valley's only 
shelter for battered women. 
</P>
<P>
 Numerous performance artists -- including Chuck Z and Shrimps -- will also 
perform at the benefit, and speakers will discuss domestic violence, which 
according to the National Organization for Women claims the lives of 10 women a 
day in the United States. 
</P>
<P>
 The jam will run from 5 to 11 p.m. at the Roxbury, 8225 Sunset Blvd. The $20 
ticket covers six hours of music, information, art and food. Tickets are 
available at the door and through TicketMaster. to charge tickets by phone, 
call (213) 480-3232. ERIC SLATER 
