<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: SANTA ANA; HEALTH AND SAFETY FAIR SET FOR FLOWER PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEE ROMNEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two dozen volunteers with the Clinton Administration's AmeriCorps program will 
offer a health and safety fair in Santa Ana's beleaguered 3rd Street 
neighborhood Saturday and Sunday to offer free child immunizations and 
identification cards for children. 
</P>
<P>
 The fair marks the first project for the AmeriCorps volunteers, who came to 
Santa Ana's nonprofit Civic Center Barrio Housing Corp. last month under 
Clinton's version of a domestic Peace Corps.The youths will be working to 
develop social programs that improve health and education and crack down on 
crime, said Helen Brown, Civic Center Barrio president. 
</P>
<P>
 The weekend fair will follow a neighborhood cleanup along 3rd Street, long 
dominated by a tough local gang and the recent focus of a five-month undercover 
police operation that landed many gang members in jail. 
</P>
<P>
 The free event will take place in Flower Park on Flower and 3rd streets from 
10 a.m. to 4 p.m. Orange County Health Services employees will be offering 
immunizations for rubella, polio and hepatitis B. There will also be free 
dental screening and other health services. Parents must be present for child 
immunizations.  
</P>
<P>
 The fair also will feature face painting, a mobile library and mobile museum, 
and "Barney," the talking police car. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, contact AmeriCorps Community Builders at (714) 835-0406. 
LEE ROMNEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
