<P>
GLENDALE / BURBANK FOCUS: HOSPITAL OFFERS FREE FLU SHOTS TO SENIORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ERIC SLATER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 If the arrival of flu season is not especially cheery news, Glendale Adventist 
Medical Center is softening the blow by offering free flu shots to seniors. 
</P>
<P>
 The center will immunize 200 Glendale residents, 60 and older, at no cost 
Monday and Tuesday from 8 a.m. to 2 p.m. The shots will be given on a 
first-come, first-served basis in the emergency department at the hospital, 
1509 Wilson Terrace. 
</P>
<P>
 Those who are allergic to eggs, are ill or have a fever, and pregnant women 
should not be vaccinated, the hospital said. 
</P>
<P>
 Medical experts suggest that seniors be immunized to prevent or lessen the 
effects of influenza, and say those with health problems, including diabetes, 
heart conditions, high blood pressure or respiratory problems, are especially 
vulnerable to the virus. 
</P>
<P>
 Parking will be available in the outpatient parking area. For more 
information, call (818) 409-8202. ERIC SLATER 
</P>
</TEXT>
