<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; YOUTH KILLED IN HIGH-SPEED CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Lancaster teen-ager was killed Thursday when he lost control of his car, 
swerved into oncoming traffic and collided with a truck, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The noontime accident occurred when the youth, 18, tried to pass a car while 
driving south on Sierra Highway near Avenue D at about 80 m.p.h., witnesses 
told investigators.Seeing northbound traffic closing in on him, he veered back 
into the southbound lane. He lost control and collided head on with a truck in 
the southbound lane, which had veered across the road in an attempt to avoid 
him, said Officer Richard Perez of the California Highway Patrol. 
</P>
<P>
 The youth, whose name was not immediately available, was thrown from the car 
and died at the scene, Perez said. The driver of the truck was treated at 
Antelope Valley Hospital for minor injuries. 
