<TEXT>
<P>
 A toddler was crushed Thursday when she was thrown from her mother's car and 
it overturned on her, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Rachel Borunda, 21 months old, was killed on 110 Street East at Avenue Q just 
after noon when her mother's car drifted to the shoulder of the road and 
overturned, said Officer Richard Perez of the California Highway Patrol. 
</P>
<P>
 Both Rachel and her mother were thrown from the car but it rolled over the 
child, Perez said. She was declared dead at Desert Palms Hospital in Palmdale. 
</P>
<P>
 The mother, who was not injured, told investigators that the child was 
strapped in by a seat belt but was not in a car seat, Perez said. The 
investigation will continue, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
