<HEADLINE>
<P>
PERRANOSKI TO COACH WITH GIANTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ron Perranoski, fired as Dodger pitching coach in September, was named minor 
league pitching coordinator by the San Francisco Giants on Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Perranoski had been a coach in the Dodger organization since retiring in 1973 
after 13 seasons as a relief pitcher. He was the Dodgers' major league pitching 
coach for 14 seasons and a minor league pitching coach for seven years before 
that. 
</P>
<P>
 Perranoski's firing came as a surprise. As pitching coach, his staffs finished 
with the first- or second-best earned run averages in the National League nine 
times. 
</P>
<P>
 Perranoski was replaced by Dave Wallace after Fred Claire, executive vice 
president, decided that Wallace could better relate to the Dodgers' younger 
pitchers. 
</P>
