<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOLLYWOOD PARK; MISNOMER WINS FEATURE ON DIRT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL CHRISTINE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rain made a 1 1/16-mile dirt race out of what was scheduled to be a mile on 
the grass Thursday at Hollywood Park, and favored Misnomer was a two-length 
winner in the Precisionist Stakes. 
</P>
<P>
 Hunt For Missouri, a maiden, was scratched and might run in Sunday's $100,000 
Hollywood Prevue Breeders' Cup Stakes. 
</P>
<P>
 Chris Antley rode three winners Thursday. BILL CHRISTINE 
</P>
