</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Buena High's chances of winning the Channel League title outright were ruined 
when San Marcos scored in the second half to steal a 7-6 victory Thursday 
night. 
</P>
<P>
 Running back Nathan Ridgell scored on a 60-yard run to tie the score, 6-6, 
with 9 minutes 25 seconds remaining in the third quarter.Alfredo Moreno kicked 
the decisive extra point for San Marcos (6-4, 5-2 in league play). 
</P>
<P>
 With eight minutes remaining in the first half, Buena linebacker Damon Deck 
forced a fumble and recovered it at the San Marcos 16-yard line. 
</P>
