<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA / FRIDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; LAGUNA BEACH COMES BACK TO DEFEAT 
ESTANCIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RICK CHRISTOPHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nate Pivaroff's 11-yard run with under three minutes left gave Laguna Beach a 
22-20 victory over Estancia in a Pacific Coast League game Thursday at Laguna 
Beach High School. 
</P>
<P>
 Starting at their 47, the Artists drove 53 yards in four plays, sparked by a 
30-yard screen pass from Pivaroff to Ryan Steel. 
</P>
<P>
 The come-from-behind victory spoiled an impressive performance by Estancia's 
running tandem of Carlo Amaya and Bachy Gonzalez. 
</P>
<P>
 Amaya led the Eagles with three touchdowns and 113 yards rushing; Gonzalez 
added a game-high 139 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach led, 7-0, on Pivaroff's one-yard sneak set up by Steel's 24-yard 
run to the one-yard line. 
</P>
<P>
 Taking advantage of two out-of-bounds kickoffs to start the third quarter, 
Estancia drove 60 yards in six plays for its first score. Amaya's five-yard run 
and a two-point conversion run by Gonzalez gave Estancia its first lead, 8-7, 
minutes into the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 Two plays later, Pivaroff hit Zeda Stone with a 63-yard touchdown pass to 
regain a 13-8 lead. Stone caught a game-high five catches for 99 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Amaya's second score, a one-yard run, put the Eagles ahead, 14-13, going into 
the fourth quarter. His 11-yard run with 4:18 left gave Estancia a 20-16 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Pivaroff threw for 236 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach finishes its season 2-8, 1-4 in league. Estancia is 4-6, 1-4. 
RICK CHRISTOPHER 
</P>
</TEXT>
