<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA / FRIDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; EMPIRE LEAGUE; HUSKEY OVERCOMES JITTERS, 
LIFTS CYPRESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RUSSELL BANKS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bryan Huskey was nervous. He had a right to be. 
</P>
<P>
 Huskey kicked a 27-yard field goal with six seconds left as Cypress beat 
Katella, 17-15, Thursday night in Empire League play at Western High School. 
</P>
<P>
 "I was nervous," Huskey said. "When I went to plant my foot, I slipped and hit 
the (kicking) tee." 
</P>
<P>
 The ball had just enough to clear the crossbar, but at first it didn't seem 
like enough for Cypress (3-7, 1-4).  
</P>
<P>
 Especially not after Katella (0-10, 0-5) drove down and Josh Welton kicked a 
27-yard field goal with 59 seconds remaining to give the Knights a 15-14 lead 
and an apparent victory.  
</P>
<P>
 Cypress came back on the passing of David Wheeler. The senior quarterback hit 
two key passes on the final drive. 
</P>
<P>
 Wheeler passed 22 yards to Bobby Brito and then hit Huskey for 19 more yards 
to the Katella 22-yard line. 
</P>
<P>
 Three plays later, Huskey knocked out the Knights. 
</P>
<P>
 Katella got off to a quick start when it took the opening kickoff and scored 
in four plays. Sal Viramontes scored on a 20-yard run. Viramontes rushed for 97 
yards in 13 carries. 
</P>
<P>
 Wheeler hit Brito with a three-yard touchdown pass with 51 seconds left in the 
first quarter to give Cypress a 7-6 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Greg Cleave ran 72 yards for a third-quarter score. Cleave finished with 151 
yards in 16 carries for Cypress. 
</P>
<P>
 Welton caught an eight-yard pass from Viramontes late in the third quarter. 
RUSSELL BANKS 
</P>
</TEXT>
