<HEADLINE>
<P>
RESEDA FOLLOWS RUTTER, 42-14 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES TEMMEL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Senior quarterback Matt Rutter completed eight of 13 passes for 119 yards and 
two touchdowns and ran for another score Thursday night to lead Reseda High to 
a 42-14 victory over Monroe in a Valley Pac-8 Conference game. 
</P>
<P>
 Reseda jumped to a 14-0 lead when Rutter hooked up with tight end Alonso 
Arreola on a pair of first-half touchdowns.The first covered 24 yards and 
completed a 10-play, 74-yard opening drive. 
</P>
<P>
 Five minutes later, Rutter hit Arreola on a 38-yard scoring pass. Monroe 
closed within 14-7 in the second quarter when Jesse Jones scored from 58 yards 
on his first carry. Jones finished with 117 yards in 11 carries. 
</P>
<P>
 Reseda (7-3, 6-1 in conference play) opened the second half by scoring 21 
consecutive points. Rutter scored on a three-yard run and tailback Charles 
Shells (14 carries, 80 yards) added touchdown runs of six yards and one yard 
for a 35-14 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Nick Nuccitelli scored on a 13-yard run in the fourth quarter for Monroe (5-5, 
4-3). Nuccitelli finished with 136 yards in 14 carries. JAMES TEMMEL 
</P>
</TEXT>
