<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCOTT AND MOJICA NAMED CO-COACHES AT VERDUGO HILLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVE DESMOND 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Don Scott Jr. and Sal Mojica have been named co-coaches of the Verdugo Hills 
High football team, Principal Gary Turner announced Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 They will replace Buzz Johnson, who announced his resignation last week, 
citing health and personal reasons. 
</P>
<P>
 Verdugo Hills, which on Thursday lost its season finale against Hollywood, 
21-12, finished 1-7-2 . The Dons were 5-23-3 in Johnson's three seasons as 
coach. 
</P>
<P>
 Scott and Mojica coached Verdugo Hills' frosh-soph team to a 9-1 record this 
season. 
</P>
<P>
 Scott is the son of Verdugo Hills Athletic Director Don Scott Sr. 
</P>
<P>
 Don Scott Jr. graduated from Verdugo Hills in 1985 and was a linebacker at 
Glendale College and Cal State Northridge. DAVE DESMOND 
</P>
</TEXT>
