<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; SYLMAR STAYS UNDEFEATED WITH 59-0 ROUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE GALLUZZO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Running back Durell Price and receiver Davon Young each scored three 
touchdowns to lead Sylmar High to a 59-0 rout of Grant in a Valley Pac-8 
Conference finale Thursday night at Sylmar. 
</P>
<P>
 Sylmar (10-0, 7-0), which has won 39 consecutive conference games since 1988, 
clinched the East Valley League title outright for the fifth season in a row 
and is expected to be seeded first in the City Section Division 4-A 
playoffs.Sylmar is the only undefeated team in the section. 
</P>
<P>
 Price, who rushed for 62 yards, scored on three of his six carries on runs of 
27, two and three yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Young returned a punt 57 yards for the first Sylmar score and added touchdown 
receptions of 19 and 68 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Sylmar's swarming defense knocked two Grant starters out of the game in the 
first half. Quarterback Adam Crespo left the game late in the first quarter 
because of a leg injury and was taken to the hospital by ambulance. Running 
back Di-Onte Smith, who entered the game with 1,584 yards rushing and 18 
touchdowns, was held to a season-low 19 yards in nine carries and left the game 
in the second quarter because of a leg injury and did not return. 
</P>
<P>
 Grant (2-7-1, 1-6) completed only two passes for five yards against a Sylmar 
defense that forced three fumbles and posted its fifth shutout. 
</P>
<P>
 Sylmar quarterback Greg Marquez completed six of nine passes for 132 yards and 
two touchdowns in three quarters of work to fuel a 53-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Gerrod Taylor rushed for 57 yards in three carries and scored on runs of 46 
and four yards. STEVE GALLUZZO 
</P>
