<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA / FRIDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; ARROWHEAD LEAGUE; SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA 
CHRISTIAN STILL HAS HOPE AFTER VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Southern California Christian kept its slim playoff hopes alive with a 12-8 
victory over La Verne Lutheran Thursday night in an Arrowhead League game. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to their victory, the Flames (3-7, 2-3) also need a Hesperia 
Christian victory at Arrowhead Christian tonight, which would put the three 
teams into a three-way tie for third place in the league.The winner of a coin 
flip would then advance. 
</P>
<P>
 "We'd love to go, but I'm not sure we are ready for playoff-caliber 
competition," Flames Coach Bert Esposito said. "But we'll take it." 
</P>
<P>
 The Flames scored two touchdowns on their first three possessions. 
</P>
<P>
 Steve Schinofen's one-yard quarterback sneak with 6 minutes 5 seconds left in 
the first quarter gave the Flames a 6-0 lead. The opening drive covered 62 
yards and the key play was a 40-yard pass from Schinofen to Jeremy Smith that 
advanced the ball to the La Verne six-yard line. 
</P>
<P>
 With 7:31 left in the first half, Mark Caballero went up the middle for an 
11-yard touchdown and a 12-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 The Trojans (2-8, 0-5) scored on their first possession of the second half 
when Matt Keller pounded it in from three yards. Keller ran in for two points 
and La Varne trailed, 12-8, with 8:56 left in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 The Flames were able to shut out the Trojans the rest of the way with Manny 
Marquez, Ben Morookian and Ken Buhler making key stops on fourth-down plays. 
</P>
<P>
 Caballero led the SCC offense, rushing 15 times for 52 yards. Ken Thomason led 
La Verne with 92 yards in 18 carries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
