<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA / FRIDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; FAST START NETS VICTORY, PLAYOFFS FOR 
EDISON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATT FARMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 At the very least, Edison proved Thursday night it's the third-best team in 
the Sunset League. 
</P>
<P>
 The Chargers (8-2, 3-2) earned the final automatic playoff qualifying berth by 
virtue of a 26-16 victory over Marina at Huntington Beach High School in front 
of a homecoming crowd of 2,000. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're 8-2 and the two games we lost were Los Al and Esperanza," Edison Coach 
Dave White said. "Somebody's going to have to be tough to beat us in the 
playoffs." 
</P>
<P>
 Quarterback Pat Markovsky led the Charger attack, completing 17 of 29 passes 
for 219 yards and two touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 The Chargers took an early lead, as Brad Lisotto ran in from two yards with 4 
minutes 19 seconds remaining in the first quarter. But the Vikings came back on 
their next possession with a 20-yard field goal from Peter Mignosa. 
</P>
<P>
 Markovsky connected with Mike Ogas for a 38-yard touchdown pass and Lisotto 
added another two-yard run to put Edison ahead, 20-3. 
</P>
<P>
 Marina (6-4, 1-4) battled back, as Viking Steve Cooper recovered a shanked 
punt at the Edison three-yard line and ran it into the end zone to cut the 
Charger lead to 20-10 at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
 Both teams scored in the second half, but Marina could not draw closer as 
Edison shut down the Viking running attack in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 The Chargers compiled 339 yards in total offense, besting the 291-yard effort 
from Marina. 
</P>
<P>
 Mike Williams rushed for 130 yards in 19 carries to lead Marina. MATT FARMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
