<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA / FRIDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; SANTIAGO GETS GARDEN GROVE ON THE RUN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ERIC MADDY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Santiago moved one step closer to a playoff berth Thursday night, knocking off 
host Garden Grove, 27-13, in the regular season finale for both teams. 
</P>
<P>
 The Cavaliers (4-6, 3-3), who won only one game in the last two seasons, moved 
into a tie with Garden Grove (4-5, 3-3) in the league standings.If Pacifica 
(5-4, 3-2) losses to Los Amigos tonight, the three teams would flip coins to 
determine the third playoff team from the league. Rancho Alamitos and Los 
Amigos have already clinched the top two spots. 
</P>
<P>
 Garden Grove fumbled on its first play from scrimmage, and Ivan Kim recovered 
at the Argonaut 24. Tommy Sokanthong scored from seven yards out four plays 
later and Santiago led, 7-0. 
</P>
<P>
 Sokanthong blocked a Ryan Cleary field-goal attempt on the next Argonaut 
possession, leading to a 61-yard scoring pass from Christian Cortez to Octavio 
Villa and a 14-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Garden Grove would score twice before the half, getting scoring runs of 22 
yards from Manuel Millan and three yards from Ruben Reyna. The conversion on 
the second score failed, leaving Santiago with a 14-13 lead at the half. 
</P>
<P>
 The Argonauts never got any offense going in the second half, gaining only 49 
yards and turning the ball over three times. Santiago upped the lead to 21-13 
on a six-yard Anthony Callari run early in the fourth quarter. ERIC MADDY 
</P>
</TEXT>
