<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA / FRIDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; SEA VIEW LEAGUE; CORONA DEL MAR SQUEEZES 
BY WOODBRIDGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Corona del Mar held off a late Woodbridge rally to post a 7-6 Sea View League 
victory and clinch a Southern Section playoff berth Thursday night at Irvine 
High. 
</P>
<P>
 Corona del Mar improved to 5-5 overall and 3-2 in League.If Irvine wins its 
game Saturday against Santa Margarita, the Sea Kings will finish in third 
place. If the Vaqueros lose, Corona del Mar will finish second. 
</P>
<P>
 Woodbridge (5-5, 0-5) had a chance to win the game in the final minute. 
</P>
<P>
 The Warriors took over on their 15-yard line with two minutes remaining and 
marched the ball to the Corona del Mar 32. 
</P>
<P>
 But Woodbridge eventually ran short on time. As time expired, Nathan Bennett's 
52-yard field goal fell short. 
</P>
<P>
 Corona del Mar took a 7-0 lead when quarterback Josh Walz connected with Miles 
Davis on a 65-yard touchdown pass with 5:59 remaining in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
 But Woodbridge closed the gap to 7-6 on a seven-yard touchdown run by Theo 
Wakefield with 1:35 remaining in the half. However, Bennett missed the 
point-after kick. 
</P>
<P>
 Woodbridge had a chance to go ahead early in the fourth quarter when it 
advanced the ball to the Corona del Mar 11. 
</P>
<P>
 But Darren MacDonald intercepted a pass at the Sea King six-yard line. 
</P>
</TEXT>
