<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA / FRIDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; YOUNG, RANCHO ALAMITOS POUND BOLSA GRANDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANDY EISER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chris Young rushed for 186 yards and five touchdowns as Rancho Alamitos 
rounded out an unbeaten Garden Grove League season with a 50-0 rout of Bolsa 
Grande Thursday at Bolsa Grande High School. 
</P>
<P>
 The Vaqueros (7-2-1, 6-0 in league) scored twice in the game's first five 
minutes, as John Frank connected on touchdown passes to Aaron Trigg for 57 
yards and Jeff Turbarg for 36 yards.Young then added a 26-yard scoring run in 
the final minute to give Rancho Alamitos a 20-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Young displayed his versatility as a two-way player in the second quarter, 
recording touchdown runs of 11 and one yard, and intercepting a David Price 
pass and sacking him. Young's sack forced the Matadors (2-8, 1-5) to punt, 
setting up the Vaqueros' final possession of the half and an eventual 35-yard 
field goal by Frank that made it 37-0. 
</P>
<P>
 Young capped Rancho Alamitos' next two possessions with one- and five-yard 
scoring runs, but Kevin Allen and Leo Kosi assumed the bulk of the second-half 
rushing for the Vaqueros. Allen gained 67 of his 102 yards after the half; Kosi 
entered the game after halftime and gained 85 yards in 12 carries. 
</P>
<P>
 Price, playing catch-up all night, finished a frustrating three for 14 passing 
for 44 yards and three interceptions. ANDY EISER 
</P>
</TEXT>
