<HEADLINE>
<P>
IRVINE, EDISON GIRLS' TO START RUNS FOR TITLES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATT FARMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Irvine and Edison girls' cross-country teams, ranked No. 1 and 3 in the 
final Orange County Sportswriters' poll, begin their quests for back-to-back 
State championships at the Southern Section preliminaries Saturday at Mt. San 
Antonio College. 
</P>
<P>
 Competition begins at 7:30 a.m., with a Division I girls' race finishing the 
day at 3:42 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The top three teams from each race, of which there are 32 Saturday, and the 
top two individual runners not on one of the top three teams, advance to the 
Southern Section finals, Nov. 19 at Mt. San Antonio College. 
</P>
<P>
 Edison remains the favorite in Division II, but should receive stiff 
competition from Trabuco Hills (No. 4), the South Coast League champion, and 
Aliso Niguel (No. 8). 
</P>
<P>
 The most competitive boys' race of the day figures to be in Division III at 8 
a.m., when El Modena (No. 7), La Habra (No. 8), Santa Margarita and Brea-Olinda 
meet. MATT FARMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
