PHEBUS, TOP PLAYERS ADVANCE IN REGIONAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The seven top-seeded singles players, including No. 1 Keri Phebus of UCLA, 
advanced to the second round of the Rolex ITA Southern California women's 
tennis regional Thursday at UC Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 Phebus beat Amelia White of UC Santa Barbara, 6-1, 6-1. UC Irvine's Nina 
Basica lost to Arizona's Betsy Miringoff, 6-4, 6-2. Thursday's doubles matches 
were postponed until today because of rain. 
</P>
