<HEADLINE>
<P>
RICHARDSON SIGNS WITH BOISE STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BRYAN RODGERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Agoura High's Ben Richardson has signed a letter of intent to play basketball 
at Boise State. 
</P>
<P>
 Richardson, a four-year letterman who is 6-foot-6, is expected to play guard 
and forward at Boise. He is the first basketball player from Agoura High to 
receive a Division I scholarship, according to his coach, Kevin Pasky. He 
averaged 11 points, 6.3 rebounds and two blocked shots as a junior. 
</P>
<P>
 "Boise has been to the (NCAA tournament) and that is interesting," Richardson 
said. "Plus they are planning a move to the Big West Conference in 1996 and 
that definitely played a part in my decision." BRYAN RODGERS 
</P>
