<P>
BREA-OLINDA'S MOULIN SIGNS WITH TITANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lee Moulin, a two-year starter for Brea-Olinda High, has signed a letter of 
intent to play women's basketball at Cal State Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 Moulin averaged 13 points, 10 rebounds and six assists last season. She shot 
48% from the field. Moulin is the fourth player signed by Coach Deborah Ayres 
during the early signing period. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Lisa Ravensberg, a middle blocker at Laguna Beach High, orally committed to 
the University of San Diego to play volleyball, Artist Coach Michael Soylular 
said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Ravensberg, a 6-foot-1 senior, was a first-team All-Pacific Coast League 
selection last season. She also considered UCLA, California, San Jose State and 
Georgetown. 
</P>
