<P>
PREP GIRLS' TENNIS PLAYOFFS; DOUBLES CAUSE NO TROUBLE FOR MARINA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Marina's doubles teams were the deciding factor in its 10-8 upset over El 
Modena in a first-round Division II girls' tennis match Thursday at El Modena. 
</P>
<P>
 The No. 1 doubles team of Richelle Page and Alison Rimpau got things going for 
the Vikings, winning their sets, 7-5, 6-3, 6-0. Marina's Nos. 2 and 3 doubles 
teams also won their sets. 
</P>
<P>
 Except for sophomore Audrey Evangelista, who won one set against Hollie 
Fruedenberg, Marina's single players lost all their sets. El Modena's 
top-seeded Brandi Fruedenberg swept her sets, 6-0, 6-1, 6-0. 
</P>
<P>
 Marina (12-9) will play Laguna Beach Saturday in second-round play. 
</P>
<P>
 In other Division II tennis: 
</P>
<P>
 Edison 18, Redondo 0 -- Cynthia Torday and Lucinda Yeung swept their doubles 
sets without losing a game for Edison (13-6). Teammate Kelly Foster also didn't 
lose a game in her sweep. The Chargers will next face the winner of the Roland 
Heights Rowland-Redlands match. 
</P>
