<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP WATER POLO PLAYOFFS; EL TORO EDGES VILLA PARK, 8-7 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAN ARRITT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 El Toro's last-second steal preserved an 8-7 victory over Villa Park in a 
Southern Section Division I first-round water polo game Thursday at Corona del 
Mar High. 
</P>
<P>
 The two-time defending Division I champion Chargers (16-11) extended their 
playoff winning streak to 23 games, spoiling Villa Park Coach Jeff Ehrlich's 
bid for his 400th victory in 21 seasons at the school. 
</P>
<P>
 Another milestone was reached as Allen Basso led El Toro with five goals, 
giving him 134 for the season to break J.P. Mathot's single-season school 
record of 132 set in 1992. 
</P>
<P>
 Basso, one of only two seniors on the team, scored three goals in the first 
quarter as the Chargers built a 5-1 lead. However, Villa Park (20-8) cut the 
lead to one on Philip Johnson's goal with three minutes left in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
 El Toro, ranked ninth in Orange County, took an 8-4 lead midway through the 
fourth quarter, but again the sixth-ranked Spartans rallied to within one on 
Peter Cornue's fifth goal with 1:05 left. 
</P>
<P>
 After a Charger turnover, El Toro's Shane Lindstrom was able to steal the ball 
from Aaron Waldrip in front of the goal with seven seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
 El Toro will play host to third-seeded Long Beach Wilson in the second round 
Tuesday. DAN ARRITT 
</P>
</TEXT>
